{"id":89152,"title":"[Case report of successful treatment of the patient with stab wound of the neck complicated with massive blood loss and shock].","abstract":"The article deals with a case report of successful treatment of patient with massive blood loss and shock. The observation showed that use of balanced crystalloid solution and modified gelatin 4% in the program of infusion therapy effectively corrects systemic haemodynamics and effect on haemostasis, electrolyte and acid-base balance.","date":"2014-04-22","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24749315","annotations":[{"name":"Electrolyte","weight":0.826513,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrolyte"},{"name":"Intravenous therapy","weight":0.79432,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intravenous_therapy"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.764913,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.762559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.688541,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.685627,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Wound","weight":0.667165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wound"},{"name":"Shock (circulatory)","weight":0.614906,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shock_(circulatory)"},{"name":"Gelatin","weight":0.415136,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gelatin"},{"name":"Hemostasis","weight":0.365993,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemostasis"},{"name":"Hemodynamics","weight":0.350046,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hemodynamics"},{"name":"Infusion","weight":0.159122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infusion"},{"name":"Solution","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solution"},{"name":"Systemic disease","weight":0.071742